sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant NotebookPod as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant JupyterLab as JupyterLab Process<br/>localhost HTTP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PyPI as PyPI Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,JupyterLab: Flow 1: User Accesses Jupyter Notebook

    User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/lab<br/>Protocol: HTTPS/TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: OpenShift Session Cookie
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward request<br/>Port: 8443/TCP<br/>Protocol: HTTPS/TLS 1.2+

    alt User not authenticated
        OAuthProxy-->>User: Redirect to OpenShift OAuth login
        User->>OAuthProxy: Login with credentials
    end

    OAuthProxy->>OAuthProxy: Validate OAuth2 Bearer Token<br/>Check user owns notebook or has admin role

    OAuthProxy->>NotebookPod: Proxy request<br/>Port: 8888/TCP<br/>Protocol: HTTP (same pod)<br/>Auth: None (authenticated by proxy)
    NotebookPod->>JupyterLab: Forward to JupyterLab<br/>localhost HTTP
    JupyterLab-->>NotebookPod: JupyterLab UI HTML
    NotebookPod-->>OAuthProxy: Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: JupyterLab Interface

    Note over User,S3: Flow 2: Notebook Pulls Data from S3

    User->>JupyterLab: Execute Python code<br/>import boto3 and fetch S3 object
    JupyterLab->>JupyterLab: Load AWS credentials<br/>from mounted Secret
    JupyterLab->>S3: GET /bucket/data.csv<br/>Port: 443/TCP<br/>Protocol: HTTPS/TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM Credentials
    S3-->>JupyterLab: Data file
    JupyterLab-->>User: Display data in notebook

    Note over User,PyPI: Flow 3: Install Python Package at Runtime

    User->>JupyterLab: !pip install scikit-image
    JupyterLab->>PyPI: GET /simple/scikit-image/<br/>Port: 443/TCP<br/>Protocol: HTTPS/TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: None
    PyPI-->>JupyterLab: Package files
    JupyterLab->>JupyterLab: Install to /opt/app-root/src
    JupyterLab-->>User: Package installed

    Note over User,JupyterLab: Flow 4: API Request (Kernel Management)

    User->>Router: POST /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/api/kernels<br/>HTTPS/443
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward<br/>HTTPS/8443
    OAuthProxy->>NotebookPod: Proxy<br/>HTTP/8888
    NotebookPod->>JupyterLab: Start kernel request
    JupyterLab->>JupyterLab: Launch Python kernel process
    JupyterLab-->>NotebookPod: Kernel ID and status
    NotebookPod-->>OAuthProxy: JSON response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: JSON response
    Router-->>User: Kernel started
